      • queryWMI

        public static <T extends Enum<T>> WmiUtil.WmiResult<T> queryWMI(WmiUtil.WmiQuery<T> query,
                                                                int timeout)
                                                         throws TimeoutException
        Query WMI for values, with a specified timeout.
        Type Parameters:
        T - an enum implementing WmiProperty
        Parameters:
        query - A WmiQuery object encapsulating the namespace, class, properties, and timeout
        timeout - Number of milliseconds to wait for results before timing out. If EnumWbemClassObject.WBEM_INFINITE (-1), will always wait for results. If a timeout occurs, throws a TimeoutException.
        Returns:
        a WmiResult object containing the query results, wrapping an EnumMap
        Throws:
        TimeoutException - if the query times out before completion
